    <h2 class="section-title">Repair when something fails. Cleaning when scale and biofilm build up. Different problems, different solutions.</h2>

    <div class="services-split">
      <div class="service-block repair">
        <div class="sb-badge badge-repair">🔧 Mechanical Repair</div>
        <h3>When a component has failed</h3>
        <p>A part has broken, worn out, or failed — the machine won't run, won't cycle correctly, or produces no ice regardless of scale or cleanliness.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Water inlet valve failure (no water entering)</li>
          <li>Water pump failure (no distribution to evaporator)</li>
          <li>Harvest cycle failure (ice won't release from plates)</li>
          <li>Bin sensor failure (machine thinks bin is full)</li>
          <li>Refrigerant leak (machine runs but can't freeze)</li>
          <li>Compressor failure (no refrigeration at all)</li>
          <li>Condenser fan motor failure (overheating)</li>
          <li>Control board fault</li>
