    <p class="section-number">08 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Commercial ice machine service — what LA operators ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does commercial ice machine repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Commercial diagnostic is $120, applied to the repair or cleaning service if approved. Repairs run $180–$500 for component failures. Descaling service alone is $120–$200 depending on machine size. Mold sanitization service is $180–$280 and includes full disassembly and service documentation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How often should a commercial ice machine be cleaned in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Every 3–4 months for high-volume operations, every 6 months minimum for all LA commercial machines. LA water at 300–400 mg/L TDS accumulates scale 2–3x faster than manufacturer schedules assume. The 6-month schedule is the minimum, not the recommended interval for most LA restaurant environments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>There's pink or black slime in my ice machine bin — what do I do?</h3>
        <p>Stop serving ice immediately. This is bacterial or fungal contamination, not an aesthetic issue. Call us at {phone} for emergency sanitization. Do not just run the machine — contamination is throughout the water path, not only at visible surfaces. We provide written service documentation for your health inspection file.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My ice machine is producing less ice than normal — why?</h3>
        <p>In Los Angeles, mineral scale on the evaporator plates is the most common cause — coating reduces ice formation per cycle. Also check refrigerant charge, water distribution tube blockage, clogged water filter, and dirty condenser. We assess all four before recommending parts. Often a cleaning service alone restores full output.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Should I repair or replace my commercial ice machine?</h3>
        <p>Ice machines last 7–10 years with proper maintenance. Under 6 years old, repair almost always makes sense. Over 10 years with compressor failure, we'll give you an honest assessment including replacement cost. Machines with chronically neglected maintenance are often better replaced — scale and corrosion throughout the system are hard to fully reverse.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Hoshizaki, Scotsman, and Manitowoc ice machines?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Hoshizaki, Scotsman, Manitowoc, and Ice-O-Matic are the brands we service most in LA. We carry Hoshizaki parts on the van and source others same-day. EPA 608 certified for refrigerant work. All cleaning uses NSF-approved food-safe sanitizers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does the warranty cover on ice machine repairs?</h3>
        <p>Repairs carry a 90-day warranty on parts and labor. Cleaning services carry a 30-day satisfaction guarantee — if scale or contamination issues return within 30 days, we re-service at no charge. In writing before we leave.</p>
